I was detached you see, I never even felt the coming out !

1014
01:19:14,783 --> 01:19:16,408
So much detached that Christine told me

1015
01:19:16,450 --> 01:19:21,159
she was cramped up with pressure but to me it was just, just nothing.

1016
01:19:21,950 --> 01:19:32,658
Dust. So that detachment has to come.

1017
01:19:32,700 --> 01:19:37,241
Now you should know which part you are there.

1018
01:19:37,241 --> 01:19:42,867
Like idea of detachment should not be

1019
01:19:42,909 --> 01:19:47,742
that - I would say hippy style of detachment,

1020
01:19:47,783 --> 01:19:49,950
that you have right to exploit everybody else.

1021
01:19:51,909 --> 01:19:54,950
And the other type as I told you. which is very ridiculous.

1022
01:19:55,450 --> 01:19:58,491
It's not an idea, it's a thing,

1023
01:19:58,491 --> 01:20:02,408
it's your awareness itself which is detached.

1024
01:20:09,283 --> 01:20:15,283
So, these four things for your material side is important.

1025
01:20:17,408 --> 01:20:23,034
What you eat is not so important,

1026
01:20:23,075 --> 01:20:24,450
because whatever you eat,

1027
01:20:24,491 --> 01:20:26,867
if the brain is going to be such a non-sensical thing

1028
01:20:26,909 --> 01:20:30,325
it's better whether you eat it or not, makes no difference does it?

1029
01:20:30,366 --> 01:20:34,159
Analyze it, like in the hotel, what will you have,

1030
01:20:34,159 --> 01:20:36,159
" I'll have pancakes," what will you have,

1031
01:20:36,159 --> 01:20:38,283
" I'll have this I'll have that", for what ?

1032
01:20:38,825 --> 01:20:41,034
I just don't understand why waste so much energy,

1033
01:20:41,075 --> 01:20:43,700
why not you all have pancakes all of you put together.

1034
01:20:44,950 --> 01:20:49,533
It's a very big thing you know. Or, today I'll have this.

1035
01:20:49,533 --> 01:20:56,575
"I". Out of all this materialism what comes out is Mr "I".

1036
01:20:58,700 --> 01:21:01,075
So we develop this Mr I.

1037
01:21:01,700 --> 01:21:06,075
So the word "I" must go away, we should speak "we".

1038
01:21:07,825 --> 01:21:13,325
"We" means you and all the Sahaja Yogis put together.

1039
01:21:15,117 --> 01:21:19,075
When you say "we" you will find it will be different.

1040
01:21:19,075 --> 01:21:22,491
Or take your name, like "this Norman."

1041
01:21:23,533 --> 01:21:28,283
"This Norman won't listen," like children say.

1042
01:21:28,325 --> 01:21:31,950
I asked a little boy, will you go home ? "

1043
01:21:32,450 --> 01:21:39,658
I will go, but this (his name was Munna) this Munna, won't go,

1044
01:21:39,700 --> 01:21:50,117
he's very obstinate, what can I do ?" This is detachment.

1045
01:21:50,700 --> 01:21:53,159
To speak in third person is detachment,

1046
01:21:53,159 --> 01:21:58,658
in which you are not in the picture...

1047
01:21:58,700 --> 01:22:00,283
you are a witness.

1048
01:22:00,325 --> 01:22:01,491
You are the witness in the show.

1049
01:22:01,533 --> 01:22:05,325
So this detachment should work in such a way

1050
01:22:05,366 --> 01:22:07,325
that you should witness the whole show,

1051
01:22:07,325 --> 01:22:08,867
you're not involved into it.

1052
01:22:08,909 --> 01:22:13,617
But just see what happens, in collectivity also.

1053
01:22:15,199 --> 01:22:17,950
It becomes a political issue certainly,

1054
01:22:17,992 --> 01:22:22,117
in Sahaja Yoga also, political issue; nothing short of political issue!

1055
01:22:22,658 --> 01:22:29,491
We are not here fighting like union leaders.

1056
01:22:30,200 --> 01:22:34,575
We are all leaders ! Where is the time to fight?

1057
01:22:39,700 --> 01:22:43,159
Whom are we to fight , that we have to decide.

1058
01:22:43,742 --> 01:22:47,575
So, as far as all these things concerned,

1059
01:22:47,575 --> 01:22:51,700
are detachment and attachment to Spirit.

1060
01:22:54,491 --> 01:22:56,241
So we go further,

1061
01:22:56,283 --> 01:23:00,617
see now what should be our attitude on our mental level.

1062
01:23:02,366 --> 01:23:08,159
Physically you have seen that you have to develop

1063
01:23:08,159 --> 01:23:12,366
a complete detachment in these four ways that I have told you.

1064
01:23:12,992 --> 01:23:16,617
Now on your mental level what you have to do,

1065
01:23:17,366 --> 01:23:27,825
is to understand the essence of every writing,

1066
01:23:28,325 --> 01:23:33,159
try to discriminate between Vidya and avidya.

1067
01:23:33,325 --> 01:23:41,742
Because avidya will kill you, will take away your energy,

1068
01:23:42,325 --> 01:23:45,366
but vidya will sustain.

1069
01:23:45,950 --> 01:23:51,491
So try to find out books which are supporting vidya.

1070
01:23:51,950 --> 01:23:54,909
I was surprised, there is a lady Barbara,

1071
01:23:54,909 --> 01:23:56,950
she met only last time Gavin,

1072
01:23:56,950 --> 01:24:00,575
and she has written such a tremendous book, you'd be amazed!

1073
01:24:01,992 --> 01:24:05,742
I mean of such a level on Sahaja Yoga ! Very direct.

1074
01:24:05,783 --> 01:24:10,283
I'll show you that, and you know that book is now being considered

1075
01:24:10,325 --> 01:24:13,575
for giving her a.doctorate, can you believe it I

1076
01:24:13,575 --> 01:24:15,491
In an American university;

1077
01:24:15,533 --> 01:24:17,117
of course that's only possible in America.

1078
01:24:17,159 --> 01:24:23,159
But still that book has that level,

1079
01:24:23,159 --> 01:24:25,075
I was amazed at the book!

1080
01:24:25,117 --> 01:24:31,658
So try to gather nourishment, like reading Devi Mahatmya,

1081
01:24:31,700 --> 01:24:34,199
reading about, finding out about Bible

1082
01:24:34,200 --> 01:24:38,450
and finding about other scriptures, about Koran - this that,

1083
01:24:38,491 --> 01:24:41,909
and which supports you, which nourishes you.

1084
01:24:43,325 --> 01:24:51,825
Blake, Kabir, Nanaka. I mean there are so many, Laotze.

1085
01:24:52,700 --> 01:24:56,950
This is the good - is the knowledge. But you'll be amazed,

1086
01:24:56,950 --> 01:24:59,491
once you start doing it, it comes to you.

1087
01:24:59,491 --> 01:25:06,408
I met a man near Rahuri - as you know we go there,

1088
01:25:09,199 --> 01:25:12,950
and there's a man who just drives a bullock cart,

1089
01:25:13,742 --> 01:25:17,783
and he had brought the bullock cart to take me down

1090
01:25:18,241 --> 01:25:20,909
to one of the programmes, you know what we do there.

1091
01:25:20,909 --> 01:25:24,199
And he was sitting there, we were waiting, I was talking, to him.

1092
01:25:24,199 --> 01:25:27,117
And I felt an Avadhuta is sitting there to drive me,

1093
01:25:27,117 --> 01:25:30,700
I mean uneducated absolutely, he's never known books,

1094
01:25:30,742 --> 01:25:33,241
he does not know how to write, but the way he was talking I said,

1095
01:25:33,283 --> 01:25:36,366
"Oh God, from where this knowledge!

1096
01:25:41,450 --> 01:25:44,159
From where was all this coming, this wisdom!

1097
01:25:44,199 --> 01:25:45,909
Such wisdom, I tell you!''

1098
01:25:46,575 --> 01:25:50,366
Such wisdom that I was just stunned, I was stunned really!

1099
01:25:50,408 --> 01:25:54,658
From a man who is not even been to any school-college.

1100
01:25:54,700 --> 01:25:56,992
Christ did not go to any school or college.

1101
01:25:59,034 --> 01:26:01,075
Such wisdom, you can't imagine.

1102
01:26:01,117 --> 01:26:03,241
You meet him next time when you go there.

1103
01:26:03,867 --> 01:26:08,950
If somebody could translate him... you feel like touching his feet

1104
01:26:08,950 --> 01:26:11,700
the way - extremely unassuming simple man,

1105
01:26:11,700 --> 01:26:18,992
wearing a white, clean topi and clean dress and driving me down.

1106
01:26:19,200 --> 01:26:22,658
And to him this was the greatest privilege of the whole world --

1107
01:26:22,700 --> 01:26:25,992
is to drive me; he said "It must be the greatest of all --

1108
01:26:26,034 --> 01:26:28,658
something I must have done - to be able to drive you."

1109
01:26:29,200 --> 01:26:33,075
And in such simple ways he was explaining to me

1110
01:26:33,075 --> 01:26:36,159
about the character of the bullocks and the human beings --

1111
01:26:36,742 --> 01:26:40,742
just imagine! And the things he talked about,

1112
01:26:40,783 --> 01:26:43,491
if I tell you, you won't believe - so I just don't know...

1113
01:26:44,366 --> 01:26:50,742
That's the sign of a great man, he doesn't talk of frivolous things,

1114
01:26:50,742 --> 01:26:52,825
he has no time to talk about frivolous things.

1115
01:26:52,825 --> 01:26:54,408
I have seen my own grandchildren --

1116
01:26:54,450 --> 01:26:56,575
they never talk of frivolous things, they have no time,

1117
01:26:56,575 --> 01:26:58,117
they are busy, you know.

1118
01:26:58,117 --> 01:27:00,700
All the time clearing out, when they came here, they said

1119
01:27:00,700 --> 01:27:02,366
"We have to clear out this Brompton Square,

1120
01:27:02,408 --> 01:27:04,491
then we have to clear out this Knights bridge,

1121
01:27:04,491 --> 01:27:06,117
then we have to clear out this London,

1122
01:27:06,159 --> 01:27:07,909
then we have to clear out this England.

1123
01:27:07,950 --> 01:27:09,450
Where is the map of England, bring it,"

1124
01:27:09,450 --> 01:27:12,075
all the time they were busy, you see, clearing out, and then,

1125
01:27:12,117 --> 01:27:13,575
"this place is this, this place is this.

1126
01:27:13,575 --> 01:27:15,408
Oh God this horrible,

1127
01:27:15,408 --> 01:27:17,159
bring some shoes, do this do that,"

1128
01:27:17,159 --> 01:27:19,700
all the time they were busy morning till evening.

1129
01:27:19,742 --> 01:27:22,658
They would go upstairs in the room and they are busy.

1130
01:27:22,700 --> 01:27:24,450
They are busy people, they have no time to talk

1131
01:27:24,491 --> 01:27:26,034
of the mundane things and all that.

1132
01:27:26,034 --> 01:27:28,159
Then I brought some dolls and toys, for them.

1133
01:27:28,199 --> 01:27:32,241
They put all of them there and they put them, and the map there,

1134
01:27:32,241 --> 01:27:36,199
"now see now, (to dolls) now you look after, alright ?"

1135
01:27:36,241 --> 01:27:39,658
You know they're talking to dolls like that.

1136
01:27:39,700 --> 01:27:41,617
Dolls are their disciples. Teaching the dolls,

1137
01:27:41,658 --> 01:27:45,408
"you see, don't sit like this, you must sit properly, you don't know.

1138
01:27:45,408 --> 01:27:46,992
You can't bend your knees ?

1139
01:27:47,034 --> 01:27:49,034
Better learn that, you must learn to bend your knees,"

1140
01:27:49,075 --> 01:27:51,658
because dolls have straight legs!

1141
01:27:56,491 --> 01:27:59,742
And all the boys, even the little children,

1142
01:27:59,783 --> 01:28:02,825
I have seen the way they are busy all the time doing Sahaja Yoga.

1143
01:28:05,325 --> 01:28:09,366
Every level they are working.

1144
01:28:10,617 --> 01:28:16,283
As today I was telling Rustom about my own father.

1145
01:28:17,117 --> 01:28:19,075
You see, he was a learned man, of course.

1146
01:28:19,075 --> 01:28:23,992
But when he talked, he used to talk of something,

1147
01:28:23,992 --> 01:28:28,992
like I told him about the state of a person, called Sambhranta.

1148
01:28:29,575 --> 01:28:34,075
He told me that, "Human beings are very different from God.

1149
01:28:34,575 --> 01:28:38,241
When God incarnates then the Sambhranta state,

1150
01:28:38,283 --> 01:28:41,034
which is awakening between the subconscious

1151
01:28:41,075 --> 01:28:46,992
to the conscious state, is direct, you see.

1152
01:28:46,992 --> 01:28:49,200
He comes down directly But human beings

1153
01:28:49,241 --> 01:28:53,950
go this way, they never go straight.

1154
01:28:54,450 --> 01:28:56,992
See God descends, so he descends properly,

1155
01:28:57,034 --> 01:28:59,950
but ascent is always in a very separate way.

1156
01:28:59,992 --> 01:29:02,617
It goes on like this, and he gathers everything

1157
01:29:02,658 --> 01:29:06,408
that is in his subconscious, so the Sambhranta state,

1158
01:29:06,450 --> 01:29:09,742
where he is waking up, is such a dangerous thing

1159
01:29:09,742 --> 01:29:11,283
that he can gather up anything.

1160
01:29:11,325 --> 01:29:14,950
And by the time he gathers up the dreams he becomes something so funny.

1161
01:29:15,034 --> 01:29:19,909
He may look at God whom he has seen in his dream

1162
01:29:19,950 --> 01:29:23,241
like a witch, and the witch like a bird."

1163
01:29:23,867 --> 01:29:32,533
I saw him always busy. I mean to talk to him,

1164
01:29:32,533 --> 01:29:36,783
I found a companion and he found me a companion sort of a thing.

1165
01:29:36,825 --> 01:29:39,159
He could talk, because his attention was there.

1166
01:29:39,159 --> 01:29:42,075
His attention was not how every body has made their hair,

1167
01:29:42,075 --> 01:29:45,575
and how they are sitting down or what dresses they are making,

1168
01:29:45,617 --> 01:29:47,742
or what do you have in this thing - nothing.

1169
01:29:47,783 --> 01:29:53,575
His attention was on the Spirit, his own Spirit and Spirit of others.

1170
01:29:53,617 --> 01:30:01,241
And he was so dynamic in his brain that he knew your dictionary

1171
01:30:01,241 --> 01:30:02,491
by heart, I tell you.

1172
01:30:02,491 --> 01:30:04,700
He never consulted dictionary all his life --

1173
01:30:04,700 --> 01:30:08,700
neither Sanskrit nor English, and he was master of 14 languages.

1174
01:30:08,700 --> 01:30:14,825
Can you imagine! How he must have managed!

1175
01:30:14,867 --> 01:30:18,450
He used to play tennis very well, he used to swim for 3 miles every day.

1176
01:30:18,450 --> 01:30:21,992
3 miles. He had muscles that he could just lift you up. Yes!

1177
01:30:24,950 --> 01:30:29,491
Very healthy personality, healthy man.

1178
01:30:29,533 --> 01:30:31,992
Very generous, very generous.

1179
01:30:32,034 --> 01:30:34,450
Much more generous than me, so you can imagine.

1180
01:30:34,491 --> 01:30:36,992
Very generous, to him nothing mattered,

1181
01:30:37,034 --> 01:30:38,700
"alright you like it, take it".

1182
01:30:38,700 --> 01:30:42,283
He'll starve himself but he'll be generous.

1183
01:30:42,325 --> 01:30:46,200
And a man of principle.

1184
01:30:46,241 --> 01:30:51,825
So we come to the second point which is actually

1185
01:30:51,867 --> 01:30:54,617
we have started the fifth one - which is mentally

1186
01:30:54,658 --> 01:30:59,283
you must only take to things which are nourishing.

1187
01:31:03,408 --> 01:31:05,283
Through vibratory awareness you will know.

1188
01:31:05,283 --> 01:31:09,491
Ask other Sahaja Yogis, if you do not know.

1189
01:31:09,909 --> 01:31:12,491
But take nourishing things to read and not horrible,

1190
01:31:12,533 --> 01:31:14,783
detrimental to your growth.

1191
01:31:14,825 --> 01:31:17,366
If you read them, you are responsible:

1192
01:31:17,408 --> 01:31:22,241
You are real great readers I must say --

1193
01:31:22,283 --> 01:31:24,575
you ask any name, everyone knows.

1194
01:31:24,617 --> 01:31:26,408
I said who was Gropius, everyone knows.

1195
01:31:26,450 --> 01:31:28,283
You need not be an academician to tell.

1196
01:31:28,283 --> 01:31:31,950
Everyone knows, what happened, who is this, who is that.

1197
01:31:31,950 --> 01:31:35,034
Out of your seeking you have done one good thing --

1198
01:31:35,075 --> 01:31:37,491
to have read everything whether good or bad,

1199
01:31:37,491 --> 01:31:39,366
whatever it is.

1200
01:31:39,408 --> 01:31:41,700
But now after realisation, you must try to find out

1201
01:31:41,700 --> 01:31:44,199
what you have to read, what you have to know,

1202
01:31:44,199 --> 01:31:45,950
it should be nourishing.

1203
01:31:45,950 --> 01:31:49,909
Talk that is nourishing, helpful.

1204
01:31:49,950 --> 01:31:55,533
So in talk you should have compassion.

1205
01:31:55,533 --> 01:32:00,283
If you are talking to someone you should be full of compassion.

1206
01:32:00,325 --> 01:32:02,491
Sahaja Yoga is a system of compassion.

1207
01:32:02,491 --> 01:32:07,159
A Guru has to be very-very patient.

1208
01:32:07,199 --> 01:32:10,408
It is not like other Gurudom,

1209
01:32:10,825 --> 01:32:13,658
or even real Gurus had no patience.

1210
01:32:14,533 --> 01:32:19,867
This is a system where patience is the only way it will work out,

1211
01:32:19,909 --> 01:32:22,075
because no Gurus gave realisation, it is only you

1212
01:32:22,075 --> 01:32:24,533
who have to give it. And you know what is realisation.

1213
01:32:24,575 --> 01:32:29,199
The other day we met one; the fellow sitting tight.

1214
01:32:29,200 --> 01:32:37,117
They said, "We have failed Mother, we can't give him realisation,

1215
01:32:37,159 --> 01:32:38,867
it's a hopeless case". I said, "Really ?"

1216
01:32:38,867 --> 01:32:41,950
So I went there - at the end of it you see, they said,

1217
01:32:41,992 --> 01:32:43,408
"Mother there's one fellow sitting".

1218
01:32:43,450 --> 01:32:46,491
I wanted to aviod, you see, but they said.

1219
01:32:46,533 --> 01:32:52,783
Alright, so raised his Kundalini, raised it up, tied it up,

1220
01:32:52,825 --> 01:32:57,992
my hands bearing now. "Oh no, I didn't feel anything".

1221
01:32:58,034 --> 01:33:04,992
I said, this fellow is least bothered

1222
01:33:05,034 --> 01:33:07,199
how much we are working on him!

1223
01:33:07,200 --> 01:33:09,199
He's just thinking he's obliging us."

1224
01:33:09,199 --> 01:33:12,617
So then two or three people came forward, brought a light,

1225
01:33:12,617 --> 01:33:16,075
put the light before him, did bandhan here and everything:

1226
01:33:16,117 --> 01:33:20,034
Again I raised his Kundalini thrice:

1227
01:33:20,075 --> 01:33:25,950
"No, not at all... ! "it went on like that for half an hour,

1228
01:33:25,950 --> 01:33:27,283
then I gave up. I said,

1229
01:33:27,325 --> 01:33:29,075
"Sir, I'm sorry, you are too great

1230
01:33:29,075 --> 01:33:33,408
for realisation! We'll try again".

1231
01:33:33,408 --> 01:33:39,700
"I'm not convinced..." And I was fagged out,

1232
01:33:39,742 --> 01:33:43,200
I said "Really, I am convinced about you,

1233
01:33:43,241 --> 01:33:45,825
so, you allow us to go", and then I came out.

1234
01:33:45,867 --> 01:33:48,950
You have to have 'tremendous' patience and sense of humour --

1235
01:33:48,992 --> 01:33:50,867
you just can't tell him off.

1236
01:33:50,909 --> 01:33:53,283
You see if I told him ''You are good for nothing, useless,

1237
01:33:53,283 --> 01:33:57,867
you have a bad Kundalini you go away from here get away, get lost."

1238
01:33:57,867 --> 01:34:04,617
I couldn't say these things to him, I had to bear him through and not only,

1239
01:34:04,617 --> 01:34:07,825
in the end I had to say you are a great man, you see.

1240
01:34:07,867 --> 01:34:10,950
Because otherwise he would have used some other method.

1241
01:34:10,950 --> 01:34:13,658
Because, already the ego was so big

1242
01:34:13,658 --> 01:34:16,950
that with all the pins I put inside it, it could not deflate,

1243
01:34:16,950 --> 01:34:19,783
it was made of a special fibre I think !

1244
01:34:23,700 --> 01:34:26,075
It was such a difficult task.

1245
01:34:26,117 --> 01:34:29,408
So one has to know that we have to be compassionate.

1246
01:34:29,450 --> 01:34:34,075
We have to read something that nourishes our compassion.

1247
01:34:34,117 --> 01:34:39,199
Read of people who gave away everything that they had.

1248
01:34:39,200 --> 01:34:45,658
Tukarama. Read Tukarama. Tukarama was a poor man.

1249
01:34:45,700 --> 01:34:50,450
And one day he went to some place and did some good job,

1250
01:34:50,491 --> 01:34:56,034
so they gave him lots of sugar cane.

1251
01:34:56,408 --> 01:34:58,950
His children were very fond of sugar cane.

1252
01:34:59,992 --> 01:35:02,992
So on the way every child would ask, "give me one sugar cane".

1253
01:35:03,034 --> 01:35:04,450
He was giving to everyone.

1254
01:35:04,450 --> 01:35:06,241
When he came home only one was left.

1255
01:35:06,283 --> 01:35:08,783
So the children said, "we are three".

1256
01:35:08,783 --> 01:35:12,075
He said, "It's alright; next time I will bring for you,

1257
01:35:12,117 --> 01:35:15,950
share it among you three". And they had it,

1258
01:35:15,992 --> 01:35:18,825
they said, "better have it, now one more child will come

1259
01:35:18,825 --> 01:35:20,450
and this will also go away".

1260
01:35:22,992 --> 01:35:26,867
So one has to know about lives who have been giving.

1261
01:35:28,325 --> 01:35:31,408
Read about people who have been giving.

1262
01:35:32,075 --> 01:35:38,117
They gave their lives. They crucified them, they tortured them.

1263
01:35:38,159 --> 01:35:40,325
They allowed to be exploited.

1264
01:35:40,366 --> 01:35:42,408
They allowed to be poisoned.

1265
01:35:42,408 --> 01:35:46,575
Head of such sacrifice, of great sacrifices.

1266
01:35:46,617 --> 01:35:49,783
We are lucky people that we have seen all those things

1267
01:35:49,825 --> 01:35:51,325
with our own eyes.

1268
01:35:51,325 --> 01:35:54,783
But at least you be one of them, that you can at least,

1269
01:35:54,825 --> 01:36:00,325
if not see, visualise it. You can. Bring that as your principle.

1270
01:36:00,366 --> 01:36:06,617
So we move now, from detachment,

1271
01:36:06,658 --> 01:36:10,533
which I've told you four types of detachment,

1272
01:36:10,575 --> 01:36:16,450
and then I told you the nourishment of your mind

1273
01:36:17,199 --> 01:36:19,909
and nourishment to your heart.

1274
01:36:20,366 --> 01:36:27,075
Nothing nourishes more to a person than giving away.

1275
01:36:27,575 --> 01:36:32,450
Nothing nourishes your heart, your compassion,

1276
01:36:32,491 --> 01:36:34,658
unless and until you learn to give away.

1277
01:36:34,825 --> 01:36:37,075
Now will you please make a list of things,

1278
01:36:37,075 --> 01:36:43,117
"how many things you have given away in this one year, last one year".

1279
01:36:43,159 --> 01:36:44,867
I can't because it is too much.

1280
01:36:47,617 --> 01:36:51,700
Please make a list of things, "how many things",

1281
01:36:51,742 --> 01:36:56,117
except for your brains you have given away to others

1282
01:36:56,742 --> 01:37:02,533
without thinking about it, or have thought of giving.

1283
01:37:06,700 --> 01:37:10,658
Since Christmas let us say, to this Christmas.

1284
01:37:15,867 --> 01:37:23,867
Heart is opening. Think of giving.

1285
01:37:25,325 --> 01:37:31,491
On material level, other help is there to give.

1286
01:37:31,533 --> 01:37:36,575
But no, we don't even give the other help,

1287
01:37:36,992 --> 01:37:39,450
for which you don't have to spend any money.

1288
01:37:39,491 --> 01:37:41,117
Just give a hand.

1289
01:37:41,783 --> 01:37:45,909
I have seen, very easy to make out,

1290
01:37:46,491 --> 01:37:48,658
labour saving devices.

1291
01:37:50,700 --> 01:37:54,742
Now, I have come here, some will be running,

1292
01:37:54,783 --> 01:37:56,617
others are just sitting.

1293
01:37:56,617 --> 01:38:00,199
Tea is brought to them, food is brought of them everything is done.

1294
01:38:00,200 --> 01:38:03,617
They'll just put the plate also before: go and wash.

1295
01:38:09,700 --> 01:38:16,199
Its not only selfishness but it is unmannerly, unmannerly to be like this.

1296
01:38:20,034 --> 01:38:26,408
In Sahaja Yoga you have to be

1297
01:38:26,408 --> 01:38:31,200
extremely busy helping others,

1298
01:38:31,992 --> 01:38:35,241
at every point. To be helpful.

1299
01:38:36,199 --> 01:38:39,825
You know Ravi Shankar's Guru was a very great,

1300
01:38:40,825 --> 01:38:45,867
a very great man, a realized soul. He was a great person.

1301
01:38:45,867 --> 01:38:47,366
So he knew so many things.

1302
01:38:47,950 --> 01:38:53,200
And one day I was there, in the night you see, there was a doctor,

1303
01:38:53,241 --> 01:38:57,867
we were his guests in a way, for dinner we had gone there.

1304
01:38:58,199 --> 01:38:59,909
In the night the call came that,

1305
01:38:59,950 --> 01:39:02,199
"I need you very much" to the doctor.

1306
01:39:02,199 --> 01:39:03,700
The doctor said, "Now I'm tired".

1307
01:39:03,700 --> 01:39:06,034
He was another very giving person, no doubt.

1308
01:39:06,034 --> 01:39:08,283
He said, "Oh you must come, I have a big problem.

1309
01:39:08,283 --> 01:39:12,117
See I saw a little baby."

1310
01:39:12,159 --> 01:39:14,825
He said, "What baby have you found ?"

1311
01:39:14,867 --> 01:39:17,117
He said, "its a baby," he was an old man,

1312
01:39:17,159 --> 01:39:22,783
he said, "I found a baby of a deer which is suffering now,

1313
01:39:22,783 --> 01:39:26,159
and the mother is dead and nobody is to look after it."

1314
01:39:26,159 --> 01:39:30,200
So I said "Alright I'll also come with you",

1315
01:39:30,241 --> 01:39:33,533
because I knew I will touch the baby. I went with him.

1316
01:39:33,575 --> 01:39:41,366
So, he was sitting with the little thing near his heart.

1317
01:39:41,408 --> 01:39:44,450
So the doctor said, "What are you doing ?"

1318
01:39:44,491 --> 01:39:48,075
He said, "I'm trying to give him my life if possible,

1319
01:39:48,075 --> 01:39:51,617
so that when you come at least you find him alive".

1320
01:39:51,658 --> 01:39:53,992
Just like this, just love.

1321
01:39:53,992 --> 01:39:59,283
So he took out the thing - doctor - his coat and all that,

1322
01:39:59,325 --> 01:40:01,325
and he said, "alright put it down".

1323
01:40:01,366 --> 01:40:03,533
He put it down very cautiously.

1324
01:40:03,575 --> 01:40:05,283
I mean he was a realized soul, no doubt.

1325
01:40:05,283 --> 01:40:09,366
I put my hand on the thing and it came to life,

1326
01:40:09,408 --> 01:40:11,992
and it started, alright, he was very happy.

1327
01:40:12,034 --> 01:40:16,533
He said, "You are a Devi, you are a Goddess, I can tell you.

1328
01:40:16,575 --> 01:40:18,617
But one bad thing you have done." I said "What ? "

1329
01:40:18,658 --> 01:40:22,159
You are married." I said, "But Devis must marry, also."

1330
01:40:22,199 --> 01:40:25,075
He said, "No, supposing you have married a miserly man,

1331
01:40:25,075 --> 01:40:26,617
then what will happen to you ?"

1332
01:40:26,658 --> 01:40:29,408
I said, "I will see to it that, I don't marry a miserly man.

1333
01:40:31,450 --> 01:40:34,575
That would be the greatest curse."

1334
01:40:34,617 --> 01:40:37,117
He said, "I had the same type of a wife who was miserly,

1335
01:40:37,159 --> 01:40:39,825
and I got fed up with her for her miserliness."

1336
01:40:40,783 --> 01:40:44,325
So that is what it is : miserliness should be hated,

1337
01:40:44,366 --> 01:40:50,867
absolutely to be hated, absolutely to be the worst of all.

1338
01:40:50,867 --> 01:40:54,325
It's like leprosy for Sahaja Yogis. Miserliness.

1339
01:40:54,325 --> 01:40:56,575
It's saving saving pounds, you know.

1340
01:40:59,491 --> 01:41:01,909
That must go away from your mind,

1341
01:41:04,241 --> 01:41:09,825
Miserliness to yourself is good, miserliness to others is bad.

1342
01:41:09,867 --> 01:41:12,325
Gregoire told me a shocking thing.

1343
01:41:12,366 --> 01:41:14,199
He said, "this is our culture."

1344
01:41:14,200 --> 01:41:16,199
I said "Your culture ! what is it ?"

1345
01:41:16,658 --> 01:41:20,283
You see, he said that "if we go in a hotel, and if somebody is paying,

1346
01:41:20,325 --> 01:41:22,075
we start looking this side and that."

1347
01:41:22,117 --> 01:41:24,992
I said, "Really !". He said, that is very common.

1348
01:41:30,575 --> 01:41:32,742
I just cannot believe it ! This is culture!

1349
01:41:32,783 --> 01:41:35,783
It is the opposite of culture. Whatever you may call it,

1350
01:41:35,825 --> 01:41:39,200
it's not culture at all. Culture would be to come forward,

1351
01:41:39,241 --> 01:41:42,992
"Alright I'll pay". But Americans are even worse, they'll say,

1352
01:41:43,034 --> 01:41:45,658
"I paid for you yesterday, you pay today for me."

1353
01:41:47,909 --> 01:41:51,283
It's absolutely disgraceful miserliness.

1354
01:41:52,034 --> 01:41:55,533
But this is gracious; you see when somebody is paying,

1355
01:41:55,533 --> 01:41:58,325
you look on the other side. It may be gracious, I don't know,

1356
01:41:59,742 --> 01:42:04,241
whatever it is, it's just the same ; filth I tell you.

1357
01:42:04,283 --> 01:42:07,450
So compassion ; compassion at any point.

1358
01:42:07,450 --> 01:42:09,867
You may have to work till 2 o'clock, you may .

1359
01:42:09,909 --> 01:42:11,783
have to work at 4 o'clock, doesn't matter.

1360
01:42:11,825 --> 01:42:13,867
You have to work, you have to work, you have to work;

1361
01:42:13,909 --> 01:42:17,159
because compassion itself is joy giving,

1362
01:42:17,159 --> 01:42:22,283
because your Spirit is the Ocean of Compassion.

1363
01:42:22,283 --> 01:42:28,909
There is no other way, there is no other way

1364
01:42:28,909 --> 01:42:33,199
to enjoy your Spirit but to Give, to Give, to Give.

1365
01:42:33,200 --> 01:42:35,742
Doesn't matter if you have not eaten your food, doesn't matter.

1366
01:42:35,783 --> 01:42:39,117
Nothing matters.

1367
01:42:40,617 --> 01:42:46,159
Many a times a you know that I don't have food for 24 hours sometimes,

1368
01:42:46,199 --> 01:42:47,950
still I am giving.

1369
01:42:47,992 --> 01:42:50,742
Its not necessary for this body to eat,

1370
01:42:50,783 --> 01:42:55,283
the food of this body is compassion. That nourishes.

1371
01:42:57,533 --> 01:43:00,408
So you have to be miserly towards yourself,

1372
01:43:00,450 --> 01:43:02,283
but you must have compassion.

1373
01:43:03,825 --> 01:43:06,450
Heart, open your heart.

1374
01:43:07,199 --> 01:43:11,742
Open your heart first of all, for thankfulness.

1375
01:43:15,867 --> 01:43:19,658
This is the other quality one should have.

1376
01:43:19,700 --> 01:43:23,575
It's a higher quality I should say, of thankfulness to God.

1377
01:43:23,617 --> 01:43:26,658
He has given you realization. He has given you this body.

1378
01:43:26,700 --> 01:43:28,742
Do you realize that this body,

1379
01:43:28,783 --> 01:43:30,450
human body He has given to you.

1380
01:43:30,617 --> 01:43:32,992
He has given you everything. Count your blessings.

1381
01:43:34,034 --> 01:43:37,950
Even to have the morning, to enjoy it as a human being.

1382
01:43:39,199 --> 01:43:42,992
You are not in any bandhan, you are not in any pasha,

1383
01:43:43,034 --> 01:43:45,283
you are not pashus, you are not animals.

1384
01:43:45,325 --> 01:43:46,950
Animals are pashus.

1385
01:43:46,950 --> 01:43:49,200
You are free people, God has given you freedom.

1386
01:43:50,159 --> 01:43:56,533
And he has given you His realization. Sense of thankfulness.

1387
01:43:56,533 --> 01:44:00,075
But our language is such, "thank you, thank you, thank you," finished.

1388
01:44:00,117 --> 01:44:03,700
It is only in the lips, it finishes; lipservice.

1389
01:44:04,366 --> 01:44:11,117
From your heart thank Him, from your heart.

1390
01:44:11,159 --> 01:44:15,533
Not outside just go to church, "thank you. God very much,"

1391
01:44:15,575 --> 01:44:17,825
alright done, finished.

1392
01:44:21,159 --> 01:44:32,159
It's to thank Him from your heart, write praise. Praise.

1393
01:44:32,199 --> 01:44:41,283
Sing praise, "glory to God." to the great who has created us.

1394
01:44:41,950 --> 01:44:45,533
Your disciples are sitting and every moment

1395
01:44:45,533 --> 01:44:49,408
when you are talking you are thinking about Mother or about God.

1396
01:44:49,450 --> 01:44:57,450
You'll be amazed! It's only possible if you have sensitivity,

1397
01:44:58,909 --> 01:45:07,366
if you have memory. The greatest miracle of this world

1398
01:45:07,408 --> 01:45:11,700
is that everybody has to die and nobody remembers it.

1399
01:45:12,533 --> 01:45:16,199
But another one, is that everybody is blessed by God

1400
01:45:16,199 --> 01:45:18,200
but nobody knows it.

1401
01:45:18,241 --> 01:45:22,783
But you are so specially blessed.

1402
01:45:28,075 --> 01:45:31,034
So what you should do ?

1403
01:45:32,200 --> 01:45:40,075
Be in joy, be grateful, so that bliss comes to you.

1404
01:45:41,825 --> 01:45:45,533
Without thankfulness nothing is going to work out.

1405
01:45:45,575 --> 01:45:48,617
Thankful heart.

1406
01:45:48,658 --> 01:45:53,575
You need a heart that is thankful to God so that he gives you.

1407
01:45:53,617 --> 01:45:56,700
When you give others he will definitely give.

1408
01:45:56,742 --> 01:45:58,950
But don't think it is your own.

1409
01:46:01,783 --> 01:46:05,909
You are giving what God has given you.

1410
01:46:07,241 --> 01:46:13,283
So today I have told you 8-fold movement.

1411
01:46:13,283 --> 01:46:17,533
So you have become half moon, only in mind.

1412
01:46:18,825 --> 01:46:25,617
And the other half, keep it for the next 'Guru Purnima'. Alright ?

1413
